reviews: If you have intolerances, this is not for you. Gluten and lactose. Milk in te scrambled eggs, no vegetable milk, no fruit in breakfast. Nice staff. The room could be cleaner. Tablets beside beds were broken : nothing could be set on it.

The rooms were generally very small and uncomfortable. Ventilation in rolls was almost impossible. Having traveled with a large group of students, this was a huge issue.

Sadly, the kitchen staff were incredibly rude to us, even aggressive in their attitude towards us. The god food was terribly quality and portions were tiny.

The manager eventually apologized for the constant rudeness from the kitchen staff, but made no offer to compensate or improve things other than a free drink for each of the four adults in the group. I would definitely NOT return to this hostel indeed unless dmI absolutely has to.

Santiago and his crew have made sure that my stay was memorable. Great food, room, and convenience of stores and public transportation within my reach. Will recommend the place to my friends/family!!!

Had an okay stay as we faced some issues with our rooms thankfully Iyed and Mustafa were incredibly helpful and made the experience so much smoother. Particularly grateful to Iyed for being so accommodating 🙌🏻

Thanks generador Paris for the awesome stay!! It is well ubícales and here I could meet plenty of new people.
Special thanks to both my brothers, Mustafa & lyed who made my stay really pleasant, always eager to yo help me or to give recommendations.
I will definitely come again! Au revoir Paris!

I had a crap day when I checked in and made several errors in my booking but the front desk staff are literally the kindest nicest people ever. Especially Mustafa. He has 10/10 customer service. He’s super understanding and professional.

The rooms are also clean! Fresh sheets and blanket when u arrive. Bathrooms are cleaned daily. Good spot 👍🏽

Tom and Joey made an end to a very long and stressful day most welcoming. It was nice to unwind with no more streamers along strangers who felt like friends. Especially since this is my first time in a hostel, I was very wary of it all but actually I could t see myself staying in a regular hotel again. Thanks again for the hospitality!

Good and affordable Restaurant,
Nice stuff
Bad Badrooms for a high price
Better if you have a room on the higher floors
For the high price like 50 euros a night in 10 bed room is around 500per room per night there could be more clean bathrooms

People who work at Generator are very understanding and friendly. Especially, I want to thank Iyed, who was very thoughtful and who helped me with the early morning flight, cab ride and so on. Thank you, Generator! Thank you, Iyed!

Joey , Aïcha and zoey very good service , top they were very nice and accommodating , great night out and very good place for the sunset.
It was a place to go in paris with drinks not that expensive and quality of service corresponds to your expectations

A solid stay all around, really no complaints. There wasn't anything particularly exceptional about the stay, other than the building is really nice and in a beautiful part of the city. If you're looking to meet new people and socialize this probably isn't the place. Everyone kept to themselves for the most part and while there was a café downstairs it wasn't well used--which may be a plus for some people! There was storage lockers in the rooms, and for rent as well. Metro is close by. Beautiful walks closeby as well.

TL;DR Great facilities, not great social scene.

Shiva made a great cocktail, and created a. Friendly atmosphere. Thanks again man can’t wait to visit generator again. The food was great and met a few travelers along the way who I had a great time with.

Calm and peaceful location. Metro station just opposite to the hostel. Clean rooms with a comfortable aircon. Ideal for solo & budget travelers. All necessary amenities nearby; supermarket, restaurants, pharmacy etc.

No nice atmosphere, very dirty and shabby everywhere, mold and dirt in the bathroom on the walls and ceilings, they make you pay for every little extra Service (for example luggage lockers), rooftop only available for 4h a day in the evening

Great hostel with new and clean rooms. The hostel is in a very good location and the metro is close by. There is canal st. Martin like 2min walk. Big thanks to Santiago Facundo and the rest of the staff that were extremely helpful!

loved it here! staff always very helpful, the bar and the rooftop have a really good atmosphere, only thing i might have to say is prepare you pockets for expensive drinks! but overall i give it a 10/10 thank you GENTEAM ❤️

Great location (near the subway), 24hr reception; there were English speaking staff; very good breakfast price (simple but very good) super worth it; Only the cleanliness of the bathroom in the room was not good.

Had everything I needed bed/shower..and clean…the area has its own issues but the metro right outside and some great places within walking distance…..!
One other thing was the
view was’nt half bad from the room considering what I paid I’m happy.

Very Good hostel , I had no problems at all. the bedrooms were ok, the food too and the personal was ok.
At night there was a karaoke and was funny.
I think they must Have another activities.
But in general was OK.

There is no age to try a hostel, it was our children who chose, with my wife we slept in a beautiful room and its private bathroom while our children slept in a dormitory,
the staff is young and very friendly, a bohemian atmosphere, I recommend this hostel to try the experience

Great hotel, awesome bar, Mustafa is the man who works there and very professional! I will be returning very soon!

Also the music and food downstairs is very good and great option to have with the hotel.

This Hotel is simply amazing! The location is Awesome close to everything! Walking distance to Canel Saint Martin! Shayanta & Iyed where Absolutely Professional & Kind & provided me with outstanding service which made my experience all the more better! I look forward to staying here again this year when I come back to visit Paris!

Where do I even begin. There was an empty packet of chips in my bed when we checked in so clearly it hadn’t been cleaned properly, not sure how that was missed and there was gum stuck above my partners bed. We booked an ensuite room and were checked into a room without an ensuite so we had to go back down to reception to sort that out which was the last thing we wanted to do after a big travel day. We weren’t able to swap into the right room that we booked until the next day because it was booked out but the man at reception gave us some breakfast vouchers to compensate us for their mistake, but it was still annoying because we had to checkout the next morning and check back into the right room that afternoon and move all our stuff around. Once in the right room there was a girl in there who said she had booked a female dorm but was put into the mixed dorm but wasn’t confident enough to say anything to reception, so make sure you check you’re actually in the room you book as this seems to be a reoccurring issue.

There was only 2 toilets in the female bathroom and 3 showers for the whole floor, 1 of which had a broken shower door. When I read the reviews about it being dirty I thought people were exaggerating but these bathrooms are the reason shower shoes were invented. I needed a shower after my shower to be clean because they were so filthy, I don’t think they had been cleaned in weeks and it smelt so bad and there was a lack of space/hooks to put your things and I most definitely was not going to put anything on the filthy floor. There was only 1 sink and mirror that all the girls were trying to share, it was chaos even with everyone being considerate of each-other and trying not to take up too much space it was just impossible. Not to even mention there was faeces smeared all over the toilet seat and rim in the downstairs toilets attached to the cafe!

The pool table was out of order and the laundry facilities didn’t work either, although there was a laundry mat a short walk away so this didn’t matter too much. The breakfast was average and organised quite poorly, there was a buffet section and also a menu with 2 options on it that you had to line up and order and get a buzzer and wait which was a really messy way of doing it because it took ages and impatient people were que hopping and taking other peoples orders and the bar staff saw it happening and didn’t even say anything or care which felt very inconsiderate and frustrating for people who were waiting patiently in line. We only did the breakfast because we got the vouchers for being put in the wrong room the first night but don’t waste your time or money on it, there’s a bakery down the road which is 1000 times better and cheaper.

The furniture in the cafe was also extremely dirty and worn out. The whole place needed a deep clean and renovation about 10 years ago. The photos they use are clearly from a long time ago because it looks nothing like this now.

You also couldn’t bring your own food in either, my partner and I got food from the supermarket and wanted to eat it in the common area but were told we couldn’t because we had to order food from the cafe (which we had been up to that point) so that was very frustrating. They wouldn’t even let you take leftovers up to your room and were very rude about it. There’s security downstairs that check your hostel card before your allowed up the elevators and made me throw out my leftover pizza from dinner because it was ‘against there policy’. I said ‘what’s your policy on cleaning then? Because there was an empty packet of chips in my bed when we checked in!’ Leftover pizza in a box is the least of their hygiene problems. The man on reception didn’t like me having an opinion and spoke extremely rudely to me interrupting me and talking over me but when my partner went downstairs only an hour later to complain about there being no hot water (for a third night in a row) he was very nice/apologetic to him and didn’t speak to him impatiently or rudely like he had me.

There was a rooftop bar which was probably the only good thing this place has going for it, but again you had to order their food and drinks it wasn’t like a normal hostel shared space where you can bring your own food and drinks and it wasn’t an environment for solo travellers either as there was no opportunity to meet new people in shared spaces like you usually would. It was only open for 4 hours each day as well between 6-10pm which was a bit of a waste of a space and you’d definitely need a booking in the summer months because it’s also open to the public it’s not just for hostel guests.

Once we were checked into the correct room with an ensuite there was still issues, ie, the drain was broken and wouldn’t drain properly so the water would pool up above you ankles, the shower pressure was bad with no hot water (just a cold drizzle ). Also, the lights didn’t work in the hallway on the floor we stayed on so we had to use our phone torches as lights.

My partner and I aren’t picky travellers and usually love staying in hostels but I wouldn’t recommend this place to my worst enemy. We tried not to let this place ruin our Paris experience but it did seriously change it for us.

The Generator is in a good location right next to a Metro station so really easy to get around and visit the sites even if it is a little out of the main tourist areas. We had a private room with a balcony and the room was big with floor to ceiling windows along the whole length so nice and bright. The cleanliness was OK but not great in the room and around the building in general. The room was very warm even with the air conditioning on full and it was only 10°C outside so I have no idea how anyone would cope during the summer. We had to sleep with the balcony door open in the end just to get some cool air in the room. I'd probably look to stay somewhere else next time I'm in Paris but I would stay here again if I couldn't find anywhere else for a decent price.

Good to be close to a metro station. Neighborhood ok but not very interesting. Building needs renovation but satisfies basic needs. Could improve quality/cost. Towels not included, breakfast average but always the same.

Shayanta was my receptionist, he was really helpful and made the experience very easy and nice for me. The check in and check out were very smooth even though there were alot of people checking in at the same time.

Great for those who want to see the city but despite their best efforts need to sleep. Rooms are clean, guests are mostly young and nice people, security does their job. I'm missing the terrace most, the view at sunset was wonderful

The only bad thing in my stay was that one night there was no hot water, but it was fixed the next day and the receptionist kindly changed my room category for free. Santiago was his name.
everything has turned out as expected.

The staff were lovely especially tied shayanda so wellcoming the place wa a clean and well lit easy to find and overall a perfect way for a solo female to spend a night in Paris very safe overall and recommend

Generator lives up to the expectations as always, highly recommended.
Staff is lovely, amazing cappuccino, best croissants in town, thnx for the lighter guyz,
big love to Duone, Roberta, Sam and Juliam <3

Hostel with bedrooms like it was a hotel, good space and nice lock compartments, very clean bathroom with separated bath from toillet. Well connected to the city by metro, many options, located in cheap zone.

Not helpful, not resourceful, don’t even want to try to help. Asked if there were any water around, was told nothing is open and did not even try to look around if I could get some water from the jugs at the bar. Looked out for myself and managed to get myself some water to quench my thirst. The washrooms were pathetic and smelly, the worst experience of all, the rooms smellt like a sweat pot. Don’t know when was it sanitized. Highly request everyone to go elsewhere.

The bar was incredible. Lilas and Roberto made me feel at home while being 2000 miles away. Amazing experience all around. Very kind, and helpful. When I needed to know about the city Lilas had told me everything I needed to know. When I needed a good drink Roberto made the best. Definitely worth the time and very budget friendly.

We have had the most brilliant time on our holidays here! We have not wanted to step foot anywhere outside the hostel bar because of the amazing staff - I have to mention Tom, Shivam, Marion, Joey and Zoe by name because they were so incredibly helpful, accommodating and friendly. Could not recommend more! We will definitely be back.

PROs: Near a nice park, metro station, great dining; good wifi; helpful staff; USB ports and lighting by each bed. CONs: Rooms could use fresh paint, new curtains, rug cleaning. Shower was either very hot or cold. Rooftop deck too crowded and smoky to enjoy, but great view.

It was a Very nice weekend in Paris, the staff was very friendly and helpful! The communication though could be better, regarding the rooftop (when it is open), the nightclub and the welcome drink. But great all in all!

The staff here are second to none. They can’t do enough for us. We feel so lucky to stay in a place like this. Special credit must be made to Mustafa and Ola as they made our trip worthwhile. You are so lucky to have them working here!

Staff breakfast is very kindt,securite ok all staff perfect ,only bad is the hostel needs a refresh ,especially the public places are need off fast refresh ,like the carpets floors smell not good ,otherwise all ok thx for experience and see you next time

Sam Erwan Julien is a very friendly man offering great customer service through being very professional and polite. He therefore made me feel very welcome which has encouraged me to recommend the hostel to others.

They are opening a new rooftop tomorrow (8th of April)

Check in was smooth. When I returned to the room, my luggage was thrown everywhere. I complained to reception - they couldn't do anything (to be fair it was late evening). I was woken up by security at 7am to investigate the disturbance - not a pleasant experience.

In terms of marketing, it looks nice but it's run like hostels half the price. Look elsewhere

This place is lovely! Safe and chic. Me and my friend booked last minute and were pleasantly surprised. The vibes are good, the drinks are nice, but overall it’s quiet and comfortable. Made our experience in Paris amazing!

Very friendly breakfast crew with Samantha, Erwan etc Julien for example! The room was spacious, tidy, a bit spartanic, but relatively quiet. We didn't even notice the karaoke night. 🙂 Will definitely consider staying here again.

Gabriela and Jaco gave me a warm welcome
Rooms and toilets are clean
Excelent location
This place for solo travel its perfect
I spend almost 4 days and there isn't any complain
For people who speaks Spanish, it's perfect!!!

I enjoyed my stay for the most part. It was in a great location and the beds were very comfortable so I got a good nights sleep after a long trip. There was an issue with my booking at first but the manager, Jacopo was quick to apologize and make it right and make up for it - so far the best customer service I've received in France!

Folks at the bar were amazing !! So so lovely!
Thanks Samantha and Julien 💜💜✨✨
The crepes were so yummy we ate so many HIGHLY RECOMMEND good for breakky, lunch, dinner, dessert, snack, a lil munch 🖤

We just ordered some crepes and they were delicious ! Definitely recommend. Samantha and Julien helped us with our order and they were so lovely.
Really cute little spots also just to chill and enjoy a coffee.

Overall, it's a good place to stay. However, expensive drinks at the bar even considering we are in Paris. We had no hot water and this was not sorted during our 2 day visit. Make sure you have a ref number when you arrive as this created considerable delay. Staff were friendly and helpful. Overall atmosphere was relaxed. Would recommend.

Shayanta and iyed help me in my time of need. They were super nice and gave me a room late night, when I come ba k to Paris I will definitely come back here. I feel so lucky they were heree to help. Big thanks guys!

Overall experience was great. We felt very welcoming from the very first moment.
Food and drink offering in Café Fabien are short but cherry picked.
Metro station is on 2min walking distance.
Hostel also offers opportunity to rent a bike.

I booked a bed in a room for four people with bathroom, that's fine. But, after my check-out I had to use the bathroom on first floor and it was a messy. I think it's because there were a big teenager group and they were on first floor, anyway, the hostel should cleaning more times when there is big groups, because there are more people using the same bathroom. The food and the drinks at the restaurant it's kind expensive when you think about the size of it. I had a Chicken Burger and a Coca-Cola, both too small, and the Coca-Cola is dash. So, I think they should improve it.

As a positive, I recommend bringing your lock and your bath towel. The food in the restaurant was good and the breakfast was also good. The customer service at the reception was very good on the part of Margaux and Santiago. We will return in summer to visit the terrace

One of the bests hostels that I went. The space is gorgeous, the room was pretty good and the team was awesome, with a special mention to Rebecca! =D The localization is quite good also, even that is a little bit far from the most touristic centers of Paris (Louvre, Eiffel and etc) is literally VERY VERY CLOSE to the metro station (and with the metro in Paris you can go to any place that you want). Therefore, I strongly recommend a walk in the arrondissement of the hostel (the 20º) that is very pleasant and is the district in where is located the Cemitère Pére Lachase

A disappointing stay. Black mold. No sheets. No bathroom tissue. No curtains for privacy. Understaffed. Extremely dirty. 6 euro to borrow a towel. Food is by far the most expensive I have seen in a hostel. Save your money. I’m not the only guest who had these complaints (we formed a community in the lobby while we were continually asked to wait for help while the two receptionists assisted giant groups). Don’t bring your giant (or small) group here.

It’s my first time in Paris & my first time at a hostel and everyone has been so nice! I study French at home and they have been so patient speaking with me! Good flat mates, clean rooms, and exceptional service at cafe Fabian!! Big shout out to Samantha, Jr, Erwan! They’ve been great!!!

The place is beautiful, it has a dream decoration and it's like a monster hostel of 9 floors! Insane! Unfortunately the terrace is closed for the winter season, but Santiago, the receptionist opened us for s picture, thank you very much!!

Spectacular service and team! Highly recommend this hostel! One of the best hostels! Clean, good energy and located next to some really delicious local restaurants! The restaurant in the hostel has great food options, games and karaoke.

2nd time coming to this hostel and it’s great. Lovely atmosphere, free drink upon arrival, nice bar/seating area and comfortable rooms. Margeaux at the welcome desk was lovely when I arrived. Highly recommend.

Spent three nights in a female dorm and honestly was very nice. The room had a view over Paris and always was super clean for a 8 girls room!
One of the guys at the reception was super nice and made a list of best places In Paris. Santiago was his name :)
Definitely we'll come back!

Prior to booking my stay at Generator, I was staying at another hostel down the street. The two hostels were complete night and day. This was a huge upgrade from where I had been staying. Generator, from the time you walked in, smelled great, had inviting music playing, and staff/security were present. This is definitely the place for young professionals and more mature. The previous hostel I was at was crowded with teens running all over the place, the bathrooms were either out of order or not well kept. The bathrooms at Generator were pristine. Generator, you have set the bar for my future hostel stays!!

Rooftop on all pics closed almost 1/2 the year plus 1 floor hangout area closed - so only bar/breakfast place open - really bad this generator in wintertime compared to other Generator places - Internet was super low quality between 1-2 mpbs down! Location of hotel is super :-)

It's was amazing. The place it's really nice, the staff so friendly. Facundo the host he is the best. The best part of the hostel it is the bar, you can do a lot of stuff. And also the food and the drinks are great.

We spent two days at this place and it was really great. They got a nice bar downstairs and great beers and food. Rooms are clean and nice. The reception was really helpful the guy who attend us Ravindu was super kind to give nice recommendations so we could enjoy the weekend.

First time in Paris with my family and I loved this place, great location (close to the metro) and well equipped. Also, we were really pleased with all the help given by the front desk staff, especially Gabriela, she was really kind.

Very much recommended. A+ service. Staff are very courteous and friendly. Security is very good. Rooms are clean as well as bed and mattress.Food at the cafeteria and bar is affordable and had a lot of selection offered.

+Good location near by the metro.
+Well equipped hotel with storage room.
+Young staff full of empathy.
-Cleanliness was catastrophe in our room. The curtains were misused as towels. Everywhere dirt on the corners of the floor.

Cool place if you are more likely to spend money in other things rather than hotels, it was a safe area (walk at late nights and nothing happened) and so close to the metro, also, a bunch of stores around.

Sam, Erwan, Julien, and Ethan were all super helpful with serving breakfast to our group of students! :) They were very patient and kind to all our students, even though we were in a rush to get to our next activities!

It’s so amazing here!
The front desk staff were sooo nice and helpful! Great service would recommend.
shoutout to Iyed and Sebastien they were lovely to talk to and very helpful. The rooms are nice too and spacious

Easy check in and great social spot.

Reception is very kind and helpful. Especially Lilas working the bar! She is quite friendly with a positive energy and gave us great recommendations around the city.

The guys that work here are absolutely amazing! Iyed is specially kind and super welcoming. He helped me out with everything I needed, I even forgot the day i was supposed to check out and he helped me out. Facu is also amazing, he invited me to watch him play tango (i recommend).

Really loved the location. It was easy to get to right off the Metro. The stay overall was good. Great staff, fun atmosphere, friendly roommates. We appreciated the lockers and washing machines. Only complaint would be the bathrooms. The showers were covered in mold and looked extremely unsanitary and unsafe to use

At this wonderful hotel a stones throw from canal Martin, I found a friendly restaurant staff and helpful front desk. Sebastian was very attentive and helped me with navigating the city, local attractions, and getting to Orley

Stay was good and peaceful
Ravindu and magui at reception are great

Location is excellent from station so convenient to move around everywhere

Overall good experience and would recommend everyone to stay

And the area has some good dining place around as well

It's my first time traveling alone and I really needed as much support as I can. Mustafa and Iyed, thank you so much for helping me with everything. They made my trip easy for me and to go around Paris

Great professional staff at large Pocket friendly place in Paris. Location is cool and convenient. Near Gare De L'est and Jaurés. Young and hep crowd. If you are looking for a place to sleep thats clean and convenient, it is this! Can be a good option to meet new people as well!

Joey and Zoe were so kind to me. They took the time to show me non-touristy places for me, solo traveller than wanted to do some stuff with people of my age, and they did also explain me the different kinds of wine and beers that are the most popular ones in France.

This is a nice hostel, staff were really friendly and spoke good English but not as accessible as I had hoped for wheelchair users only disabled loo I found I could use was down in the bar. Showers were not at all accessible.

I really liked it. Just the breakfast was average and nothing special. I would come again. The Rooms are super and big we had two showers this was super. Easy check in and out with kind service and fast booking.

I spent a week at the generator and I had a great time. The staff were friendly and hotel clean. The chef was excellent dealing with all my allergies, peanuts, and gluten and made me something off the menu most nights. I really did appriciate this.

The staff are friendly and capable, especially Roberto, Shivam and Joey! They were amazing behind the bar and ensured that we were having a great evening. The accommodations were comfortable and rather luxurious for a hostel. 10/10, would absolutely stay here again

I have to come to Paris to my embassy and workout some paperwork and Generator was my first choice. Gabriela's level of attention was amazing and also her domain of several languages. We had a little karaoke night fully improvised and it was a great way to end the day.

This hostel has been terrible. First of all they tried to double charge us. Second the public toilets were smelling so badly. Secondly they had no shampoo or conditioner at the shower and this was not justified based on the price we had to pay for the night. We had only one towel and have no hair dryer. In order to leave your stuff they charge you. I wouldnt recommend this hostel!

Overall, it was a good experience. Nevertheless, the bedrooms need some improvements (bad matress, bathroom hygiene was not on top and there was a horrible noise coming from outside). The food is afordable but not excellent.

I cannot thank enough: Samantha, Erwan and Mouss, and all the awesome team at Staygenerator Paris for organizing a surprise for the 21 birthday of your son visiting Paris. So accommodating to all of the requests from the USA.

Merci beaucoup, thank you so much, muchas gracias a Samantha, Mouss, Erwan —and the rest of the staff from the café— for some embracing and daily cafés americanos and breakfasts at the Generator during my extended stay ♥

Very grateful with the staff of Generator Paris, them recommendations were mega accurate, that was super nice! Special mention to Facundo and Santiago, thank you very much!!!
Besides that, the stay was really nice, I will recommend it!

The staffs at the reception were very helpful and kind when I had some problems. They were empathetic and tried to help me solve my issue. Thank you to Mustafa and his colleagues!

Would definitely stay here again!

Breakfast is good enough for start your day.
If You are alone and just need a room for sleeping in it, is a good and valuable chooice.
Staff members are amazing and very attend.
Clean wc, bathroom and bedroom also.
I cant go to the rooftop but i think because is it cold now outside....
I was also every night at cafe Fabian. Nice place with nice and lovely staff and You must also drink there something...
Metrostation is about 150 meters from Generator. I used it a lot. You must buy a Paris Visite Pass for your trip days and can go quick and safe anywhere. But u must keep safe your gsm, money, and dont travel with a big backpack....
You can after check out also a locker rent by Paris du Nord, on the trainstation, it cost just 7,50 euro for a day.
Nice and cheap night can You get at Generator, i really happy with them!

The staff was very available and nice. The beds were comfortable although nothing was cleaned under them (I found a pack of kleenex and some other stuff). The room's bathroom and toilets were clean but the public ones weren't (two broken shower doors for three available on the 3rd floor).

Little attention of receptionist and unable to resolve unforeseen events.
It is unacceptable not to be able to occupy the room before eleven at night.
And when you do it, it is untidy, not cleaned and with things of the guests before?.
But the first thing you have to do when you arrive is to pay the complete reserve…… and what about all the hours that I paid and could not use my room?

Thank you Facundo for showing us the rooftop, it was lovely! He is so friendly and accommodating. Everything has been great so far, we are happy with our stay. Everything was clean and fresh. We love Facundo!

Hotel rooms OK, but don´t have common areas to chill or work, just have a restaurant. So u can´t buy food and eat at the hotel. Best part you have the metro, bus station and a suprmarket just next to the hotel. The recepction workers and very friendly and help at any time, restaurant atention not the best experience

Nice and fuctional furniture in the room, very confortable and clean.
Corridors and common areas need to be clean more often.
It does not have good sound insulation between rooms.
located against the corner of Space niemeyer

Best hostel, the crew is amazing! Mustafa is the best! , he assisted me with all of my inquiries and made my stay very pleasant and easy :) it's a definite must to come here for your travel experience in Paris ❤️

I loved this hostel, it’s been three times now that I go on it and the hostel is really cool.
The smell is always good ! The staff is so nice, I had a problem with the bed and they resolved it so quickly.
The breakfast is so good !! I took English breakfast twice and a crêpe, really tasty 😊

Bad service, after check in time we still had to wait for a room. We had to change rooms. Booked and payed for a room with private bathroom, there was no hot water so they told us we should rake a shower at the public bathroom… the room was still dusty and the toilet was used when we where not there.

Located no more than 15m walking distance from the North station.
The area isn't turistic, but was well conected with Subway line 2.
Welcoming stafff, special mention to the Spanish guy Santiago, he was very nice.
Food in a good price, but nothing special.
Karaoke night twice a week was good but not to many people participate.
Definitely coming back in summer time

Great weekend at Generator Paris in our honeymoon.
Staff was beyond nice. Santiago especially helped us with super recommendations!!!!
Cozy place with nice view over the city.
Price quality worth it!!

Very good place one of best in Paris see u next time it will be my place every time When I arrive to Paris clean place quiet close to everything u need it check in and check out anytime u want thank u for everything

Booked and entire 8 bed room for 5 people. Would have been very crowded and sweaty if dad been 8 people as room had poor ventilation. Accom very close to local train but facility quite tired and due for investment in a refresh of carpets, painting. The laundry facilities were scored 2/10 being quite inadequate for accom of this type. Staff all very helpful.
